 dependence\non $U$ present in MFA, which is invoked by an effect of giant van Hove\nsingularity. However the relative cooling power (RCP) is very close in DMFT and\nMFA for the same model parameters and goes down upon $U$ increase.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 22 Jul 2019 14:46:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-08"}
